item.title: RCR Episode 280: Cheap home computers
item.description: Panelists: Paul Hagstrom (hosting), Quinn Dunki, and Carrington Vanston Topic: 1980 In 1980, Commodore introduced the VIC-20, Sinclair introduced the ZX80, Tandy introduced the Color Computer, and HP tried to breed a computer out of calculators. Feed: https://rcrpodcast.com/feed/podcast/
